Title: Justifying it's price , disappointed with black level of this monitor.
Review:
It's a good product overall.
Pros-
1. Large 32 inch
2. Good clearity for pic and text
3. Decent viewing angle
4. IPS screen
5. Good response time, though not the best

Cons-
1. Most important is the level of black, it's not good and at this price it leaves much to be desired for.
2. Many models have IPS backlight bleeding, though no such problem in mine
3. Only 60 Hz refresh rate, however it's ok for monitor of this price but should atleast have freesync.
.
Overall a decent product. Justifying it's price but if you are a videophile the you would certainly be disappointed with black level of this monitor than that it works like a charm. For videophile and gamers who have some more money to spend, go for Acer k 281 which is not only 4k but also supports freesync though it as a TN pannel.

Title: Breath is the only element which comes when we are born and stay with us till we die.
Review:
'People Come into your life a reason, a season or a lifetime.'
.
Book Name- Think Like a Monk
Author- Jay Shetty
.
The book is teaching us how we are always busy in this world where there is nothing ours. One of the sayings I read which were that 'A monk went to a king's palace and asked him if he could stay in his hotel. The king in anger shouted it's not a hotel; it's my palace. The monk in a calm voice asks that before you whose place was this? the king told that it was his father palace. The monk asked, and before him? The king with surprised doesn't know why he is asking all this answered that before him, it was his grandfather palace. The monk replied with a simple sigh that, see everyone came and stayed here but left one day and where people come and stay and then leave we called it a Hotel.' This was a simple story but gives the best seek in this world that nothing in this world is yours. Yesterday it was of someone, Today it is yours, but tomorrow it will be someone else. So never depend on the materialistic thing in life.
Best book. It is telling how to calm in a difficult situation and how to stand in difficult climatic conditions of life.

Title: Life changing, a MUST READ.
Review: \n Thank you Jay Shetty, for this beautiful book. This book has changed my views on almost everything. I'm an undergraduate and I was in a state where I had a lot of things puzzled and a messed up mindset. After reading this book I realized that life is not just about the situations you face, it's about how you choose to face those situations. What mindset you have, what values you possess is what this book questions you. I discovered many things after reading this book. I love how Jay Shetty provided little tasks In-between each chapter, they were really helpful! I never generally write reviews, but now that I have an opportunity to actually be talking to Jay and be part of his coaching community, this is a shot worth giving. All in all, this book is a MUST READ. So grateful!\n

Title: A great book on human behaviour
Review: \n There are some books which are feel good books, and there are books which practical books. Atomic habit is one such insanely practical book which can be applied in life the moment you started reading this book. I remember a similar book I read a few years back 'The Power of Habit' by Charles Duhigg. I would say this book is a easier version than the power of habit book. Concepts are moreover similar in both the books. This book is just written in way so that it's easy to apply the learnings from the book of n daily life. The four key things for forming habits cue, craving, response, reward are discussed in detail in separate chapters. If you are looking for a great book on habit formation read this one first and then you can read 'The Power of Habit' book. Only thing I felt extra and not required is the last one or two chapters. The book could have been shorter. The reason I didn't rate it five star is because already another excellent book has been written on the similar topic by Charles Duhigg\n

Title: Good smartphone
Review:
You will love it, if this is the phone for you. I use the phone for light gaming, YouTube, music on BT headphones, occasional long phone calls or video calls, some quick photos from time to time.
In my usage I didn't have any problems yet.

Can get through the entire using 60-70% of battery with 7+ hours of screen on time.

Light gaming is not a problem gets a little warm if using for some time.
Heavy gamers don't go for this one, specially if you are concerned about throttling or frame drops, otherwise it is okay for regular games.

Primary camera is decent no big issue after updates, I only use primary camera. Wide angle is usable but not the best. I never used macro and depth.
Secondary camera is also good at this price. Note : I disable beauty modes etc, those just make your face look weird.
Attached a same photo in regular mode, not 64 ( blacked out serial number intentionally 😃 ). I'm sure that image will compress when uploading but believe me it's good.

Audio call and network quality is good. No Bluetooth or wifi issues. Dolby Atmos is good to change the equalizer to your taste.

Display has awesome contrast and colors and you can change settings for it.
Please do buy a case, the back plastic is a fingerprint magnet. Also you don't want to drop test the beautiful screen. Build quality good, but it is not that great when compared to Nokia or Samsung S or A series.

Coming from stock android the OneUI is good, it takes some time getting used to it. Miss the haptic feedback on keyboard. Do opt out of the marketing stuff in the initial setup to get the best experience. Some oneUI features are really awesome.

On software I would caution users to read online reviews before updating the Samsung updates. Most of the updates bring good features, read before install and you will be okay.

Hope this detailed review is helpful to new buyers.

Title: A value for money and perfect product.
Review:
A wonderful product that does justice to my 100 Mbps connection. I am not gonna into a detailed review, but I would like to highlight some points that were raised by some other reviewers.
1. It is ver2 of the hardware, and yes, it's designed to be sold in the US. But it does not matter since this is not a modem, but a router. It works perfectly when plugged into the lan port of your existing router/modem.
2. The range for 5GHz is not terrible. It is much lower than that of 2.4GHz but that is to be expected.
3. Speed on 5GHz throughout my double storey house does not drop beyond 50 Mbps. So, I've disabled the 2.4 band.

I have this router plugged into my ZTE Router/Modem that was provided to me by my ISP (Connect Broadband, Punjab). The modem has a GE port. Make sure that whatever you plug this into has a GE port. GE stands for Gigabit Ethernet. Without GE on your modem, this will be a waste of money for you.

Last point, make sure that you're using at least a Cat5E cable for the connection. The one supplied in the box is also 5E, but if you can get 6 that would be perfect.

5E can only supply speeds upto 100 Mbps in theory.

Hope you found this review helpful!
TitleText: a value for money and perfect product .
ReviewText: \ n a wonderful product that does justice to my 100 mbps connection . i am not gonna into a detailed review , but i would like to highlight some points that were raised by some other reviewers . \ n1 . it is ver 2 of the hardware , and yes , it 's designed to be sold in the us . but it does not matter since this is not a modem , but a router . it works perfectly when plugged into the lan port of your existing router / modem . \ n2 . the range for 5ghz is not terrible . it is much lower than that of 2 . 4 ghz but that is to be expected . \ n3 . speed on 5ghz throughout my double storey house does not drop beyond 50 mbps . so , i 've disabled the 2 . 4 band . \ n \ ni have this router plugged into my zte router / modem that was provided to me by my isp ( connect broadband , punjab ) . the modem has a ge port . make sure that whatever you plug this into has a ge port . ge stands for gigabit ethernet . without ge on your modem , this will be a waste of money for you . \ n \ nlast point , make sure that you 're using at least a cat 5e cable for the connection . the one supplied in the box is also 5e , but if you can get 6 that would be perfect . \ n \ n5e can only supply speeds upto 100 mbps in theory . \ n \ nhope you found this review helpful ! \ n

Title: This is a sweet and a humble that will fill you with happiness and nostalgia.
Review:
GRANDMA'S BAG of STORIES by SUDHA MURTY 😊😊

What is your fav Children's Book??

This book by Sudha Murty is like that warm sun that you wanna feel on a cold winter morning. It will boost your soul and spirits, fill your heart with longing and happiness & will take you back to the time when life was simpler and fun.

It is a collection of 22 short stories told by Ajji to her grandchildren Raghu, Meenu,Anand, Krishna and their neighbourhood friends. The grandchildren come to their grandparents place during their summer vacations. Their grandparents house is away from the hustle-bustle of the city life; surrounded by greenery and open field. The children however are most excited about the stories that Ajji is going to tell them during their stay with her.

The stories told by the grandmother are short & sweet moral stories. These stories deal on wide variety of topics such as importance of:
📍 hard work &honesty
📍being down to earth, being helpful & humble & content & loyal
📍having presence of mind
📍loving people unconditionally
All the stories will fill you up with hope and that feeling of content that you used to feel if your grandparents also told you stories.

The narration is very effective as you will be able to retain the stories for a long time. The tone is full of warmth. The book is woven in a way to make you feel nostalgic.The book brought back strong memories of my childhood when my brother & me used to travel to my native place with our parents to meet our grandparents during summer & winter breaks. Those memories were overwhelming. The smile that used to break on my Amma's & Dadaji's face are images that I would cherish for my lifetime. It's a shame that I lost them so early.

 This was my first Sudha Murty book & I am so glad that I picked up her book. It brought me out of my reading slump of 2 long months. It's a very sweet & a humble book. Do give it a read. You will not at all be disappointed.

Title: Finally, a smart "speaker"
Review:
I got it on sale for 3k. For the price, it offers decent sound and richer bass, compared to my much cheaper, 1.5k Bluetooth speaker, the Boat Stone 260. It works seemlessly with my smart home devices, and the app is fantastic. It yet doesn't have support with fire TV stick, but Amazon assures it'll arrive by mid-november, so that's something to look out for. The app works great, and you can control your smart home or this dot from anywhere in the world, as long both of your devices have an internet connection. It's a fun little party trick, really. I couldn't be more happier with my echo dot. Also, as you can see in the picture, I got the sophisticated looking white color ;)

Edit: It has fire TV support now, it's not the best experience, but hey - it WORKS.

Title: USED / BADLY SCRACHED PLASTIC UPPER COVER / DO NOT BUY ONLINE
Review:
Hi All,

Product came last night .
Told delivery guy need to open product as bulbs /fragile items to check if broken damaged , he said no, pay money, do later , in case any issues return.

Opened, found the packing bad, on opening the 3 boxes found all the 3 tubes having bad scratches , looks as used pieces.

Put the 3 into holder found it difficult as the the bulb holder is adjustable, so you need to first adjust the tube in which direction you want it .

Once done , then lower position to be adjusted which goes into the holder as all holder positions differ it's not in straight line .

Anyway did the adjustments , switched it on. Of th 3 , 2 had okay brightness , 3rd very dim.

So I suggest it's better to pay little higher by going to an electrical shop , checking the product and then buying, instead of online.

Even though you might end up paying 25/30 more . As this 3 pcs costed Rs. 523 (Rs. 174 each) in retail it might cost 200/225 at best.

Final verdict . DO NOT BUY ONLINE , AND SPECIALLY FROM THIS VENDOR .

Pictures attached for Reference .

Thankyou

Title: Highly Recommended. Thumbs up.
Review:
Amazing price. Installation was a breeze (it comes with two screws), and it's super fast. For productivity, SATA SSD will suffice, however, if you're doing beefier resource intensive tasks or gaming, NVMe SSD will be better for you. The 500gb fills up fast, so depending on the applications you install, you might want to get a bigger one. I'm using an 1TB crucial P1 nVme ssd as the boot drive & using this new one for application installs. Read-write speeds are really good.

I'm thinking of using this ssd in an enclosure with type c & use it as an external drive which can help me with quick transfer of data or work on the go.

Update: (week Later); I have added this ssd in a metal type enclosure by everpert which costed about Rs.950. Read-write speeds were good using a usb 3.1 cable.

Update: (8 months Later): Speeds were consistently stable 410-445 reads & 390-430 writes. observed a 2% speed boost after a recent firmware upgrade. i also ordered the 1tb ssd last week. will post the benchmarks soon.

Checkout the benchmark screenshots i posted. This SATA m,2 drive is totally worth its price.

Title: This book perfectly serves as a regular dose of motivation!
Review:
This short book ( ~125 pages) by Jeff Keller, a motivational speaker and coach, will show you how to take control and unleash your hidden potential. The book is broadly divided in three parts: Success Begins in the Mind, Watch Your Words and Heaven Helps Those Who Act. Each part is a step by step program further divided into smaller chapters which will definitely help you to change your attitude and your life!

The writing is simple, easy to understand and the author supports his arguments with use cases. The book is very relatable and encouraging. I read one chapter every night before going to bed and this book perfectly served as a regular dose of motivation. Highly recommended to everyone!

Title: This thing is a beast in a small package
Review:
My first impression: superlightweight, slim, flimsy.
The installation process was a bit long-drawn because I had to clone my HDD into the SSD (and my HDD being a 500 GB one, the cloning of one partition wasn't possible, so I had to delete all my media files)
After installing, the machine changed rapidly from being a slow, OKish PC, to this ultra-fast productivity rig. I install the Crucial Storage Executive to monitor the drive as well as 1. activate momentum cache (the software it comes packaged with recommends you activate in modern PCs to avail its full power) 2. over-provision (I didn't understand this so didn't switch it ON as the laptop performed like butter as it was).
After using for over 15 days, I would say that leave at least half of the drive you've installed Windows/any OS on empty as your SSD uses that space to speed up your machine. Also, update firmware and all drivers for your system to not bottleneck.
If you're thinking about gaming, this is not the solution you want. SSDs are a storage solution, not graphics processing. Although, if you have a GPU built-in, you will see very noticeable change in games (or for that matter, any software) installation and loading.
File copying is fast enough, not even close to the advertised 500MB/sec, but it goes up to 250 MB for large files sometimes, which is sufficient because you won't even probably see the copy bar.
Booting time reasonably fast, with very little time required by background processes to start to leave my PC for me to actually start working on.

Title: A Midas touch !
Review:
This book is not for you if you are looking for a way to escape reality by immersing into a juicy plot during the week end. This book is about you, me and anyone and everyone .It is about our life, our troubles and tribulations, our goals and the purpose of our existence. To determine our goal ( or Personal Legend as Coelho terms) and to pursue and achieve it is not difficult if we are focused because in the words of Coelho,"..... when you want something, all the universe conspires in helping you to achieve it."

The story is that of a shepard boy named, Santiago ,from Andulasia. The boy embarks upon a journey in search of a treasure that he had dreamt of. Each one of us are, infact, Santiago, unable to realise when and where we spilt 'the spoon of oil '. As you go through the book you learn that all is not lost and there is hope.

Narrated in a simple lucid manner,the story is interspersed with metaphors ,fables and allegories. Compelling, interesting and full of hope and positivity, The Alchemist is a bedrock of inspiration that instills a strong sense of faith in yourself.

Such is the power of this book that you will want to read it again and again. Paulo Coelho has an uncanny knack to soothe your soul and boost your morale. This book, in my opinion, should be read by everyone, young and old, atleast once .

Title: Bought it after a lot of comparisons.. BEST IN CLASS
Review:
I have compared all available TVs in this category and price range. This one is the best option available in this segment, simply go for it.. If you are a fan of picture quality, then you can stop your search and buy this. it’s better than many of the cheap 4K TVs in this price range.

Sound quality is average, but it does the job for a normal size living room.. I am using a Bose sound bar and it gives awesome sound output from the HDMI ARC port. All latest sound bar can be used with this TV because it has an hdmi arc port.

Sony’s quality is always been top notch, but still built quality is not top class in this TV. Quality of plastic is average and fitment is flimsy. TV is made in India, power adapter is made in Indonesia, only the remote is China made..

Connectivity is also seamless. WiFi stays connected whole day without any interruptions.
You won’t regret a Netflix HD plan with this TV, simply awesome clarity.
As of now I am very happy with the purchase. I would recommend this TV for anyone who loves clear picture.

Review:
First and foremost, I would like to talk about the seller, as I have seen many reviews on Amazon stating that don't buy an iphone on amazon or from this seller. The product delivery was really fast and I got the phone within 2 days of ordering it. Got the 128gb variant for 65000 rupees during the prime days sale. The phone was in perfect condition and brand new. I was a bit concerned after reading so many reviews on amazon that this seller can't be trusted but I will advise you to go for it.

Now about the iphone, The white colour looks amazing. This is my first iphone and I'm writing this review after using it for around 10 days.
The camera quality of this phone is superb and low light photos are just amazing, don't even try to compare it to the one plus or the high end samsung phones, they are no where near the camera quality of this iphone.
2nd Photo is a low light photo taken by this iphone.
The Battery backup is decent.
The Sound Quality is nice.
Face recognition is really fast.
Screen is amazing and you definitely don't miss the oled screen, if you are not a big tech geek, you won't even notice the difference in your day to day life.
Overall, I am totally satisfied with my iphone and you can go for it without any second thoughts.
Hope this helps ! ✌🏼

Title: A big NOO for Samsung M Series!!! Waste of money and time! 😑
Review:
Edit: The third pic shows you what I had to go through, to get the phone repaired from Samsung service centre!! No social distancing, and many were not wearing masks properly! Read on...

I wondered how Samsung is able to sell these mobiles (M series) at such an affordable prices competing with Mi, Oppo, and Vivo! Now I know the secret, it is done by lowering the “quality”! The M31 I bought for my sister did not last even a couple of months! It started as a small blue “dot” at the left corner and grown to an “inch wide” blue patch on the screen! Boom, within a week, you can not see anything on the screen except for that bluish patch that spread across. See the images.

When we visited the Samsung service centre, traveling for about 80kms, the reception was extremely poor and rude! The person standing at the store entrance said “this is not covered under warranty” without even having a technician checking what is the problem! Basically looks like they are all trained to say that line. When we insisted to check what is the problem, the technician checked and told that there is a leak of the display liquid inside the screen and is due to a damage caused by a small pin (apparently it is a very minor one, that can be seen only with the technician magnifying glasses), that we never understood. Another thing I noticed is, most of the people at the service centre are with their “Samsung M series” mobiles in hand, which confirmed that this series is manufactured with low quality hardware and people have a lot of complaints about them!!

We had to give the phone for display replacement, that costed us another ~6K on top of the 17K we spent for this! I could have bought Oneplus Nord by spending another 5K on top!! Waste of money and time 😑😑😑

It’s a clear no to buy Samsung M Series!!!

Title: This is life changing book. Must read for business development and for positive attitude.
Review:
This book gives you great arena to think, speak and act. When one feel devasted, negativity surrounded and lack potential which you hold still don't realize then you have to follow some good guidelines. This book is all about transforming an attitude that brings out best version from one. I personally love this book and the principles which it holds have seed so much positive attitude in me.
☘️
If anyone have positive attitude then their is more chances of getting his life towards smooth direction. In this era, most of us get edgy victim of negativity and lacks positive disciplines which leads to hamper down our skills. So to sharpen those blunt skills because of sheer living and responding to negativity one need to change their attitude.
It should be harmony with positive vibes to access the success of life and also beat up the unworthy stuffs out. .
☘️
Author has taken various perspective from so many others perspective to clear the odds of life.
☘️
I really like the quotes and the examples through which he has engraved the most genuine piece of positivity in the readers mind.
☘️
The analysis and over all observation is truly done and it's explained in broad sense so even a layman can understand this philosophy to adapt "Attitude is everything".
☘️
This book is suitable read for all who lacks motivation in their life but it can consider a gem piece for marketing and sales person.
☘️
I really appreciate the effort of author and his immense rich observation over few decades to come out with this prospect. 💞

Title: Absolutely Best in the price range..
Review:
Writing this review after one week of usage.
Delivery by Amazon is good. Item delivered within three days in awesome condition.
Coming to the product itself...
The look is trendy and cool. Checked the precision of spo2 measurements with oxymeterand accurate readings everytime. Same for BP and heart rate.
The step counter is as accurate as a fitbit on comparison which is 8 times costlier.
Using it for last 7 days continuously all day and night even in the shower. No glitches till now and still have 45 percent battery remaining. So I guess at least ten days of back up on full charge which is pretty decent in this price range.
The Dafit app is also very nice. Only one issue with the app so far..it is not able to sync with Google Fit. So minus one star just for that.
Overall, an awesome smartwatch in this price range. Just go for it.

Title: Redesign your lifestyle for longevity and happiness
Review:
We all want to lead a long and healthy life. Don’t we? Ikigai has all the elements to decode it.
 Ikigai is a Japanese word, translates to “ the happiness of always being busy or engaged”. The people of Okinawa live a simple outdoor life, drink green tea, and eat a healthy diet served in a special bowl that limits to their eating. The book explains that every being has an Ikigai, a journey of self-discovery and it’s worth the search. Ikigai draws attention to the lifestyle of Japanese people showcasing how they lead an optimal healthy life, filled with happiness, and longevity. The main focus is on diet, daily activities and a sense of joy. It also includes wisdom from supercentenarians(above the age of 110) from all over the world.Every individual's Ikigai is different but the search is common. Still searching for you Ikigai, no worries, smile, take a long breath and find one. I’m all praises for this book and cannot stop gushing about it. Grab it today.

Title: Great Breakfast Option
Review:
I usually skip breakfast due to hectic schedule in the morning. I know this isn't a good practice, hence, I was looking for a healthy breakfast option. Came across Yogabar Wholegrain Breakfast Muesli in the flavour dark chocolate cranberry, I just couldn't resist trying this product, and believe me it was one of my best decision.

This is a great breakfast option as it got whole grains, nuts, seeds, cranberry and dark chocolate which works as cherry on top for this muesli.

Before leaving for office, I quickly have this for my breakfast with milk and dressing of honey. This isn't only healthy but makes you feel fuller for longer.

Great breakfast option.

Title: This book will give you the key to the most awesome power within your reach!
Review:
This remarkable book has already helped readers the world over achieve the seemingly impossible just by learning how to bring the incredible force of the subconscious under their control. Now you, too, can learn these powerful techniques for changing your life simply by changing your beliefs. 

Dr. Murphy combines time-honored spiritual wisdom with cutting-edge scientific research to explain the influence of the subconscious mind on everything you do. And he presents simple, practical, and proven-effective exercises that can turn your mind into a powerful tool for improving your everyday life. Filled with inspiring real-life success stories, this invaluable user's guide to your mind will unlock the secrets to success in whatever endeavor you choose. 

Inside you'll discover how to use the subconscious mind to:
* Increase health and even cure the body of many common ailments
* Get the promotion you want, the raise you need, the recognition you deserve
* Build the confidence to do the things you never dared -- but always wanted -- to do in life
* Develop friendships and enhance existing relationships with co-workers, family, and friends
* Strengthen your marriage or primary love relationship
* Overcome phobias, compulsions, and bad habits
* Learn the secret of "eternal youth" and much, much more!

With this book as your guide, there are no LIMITS to the prosperity, happiness, and peace of mind you can achieve simply by using The Power of Your Subconscious Mind.

Title: Just don't judge it!
Review:
You all must have read the reviews regarding specs, performance etc. My review is based on view point of a normal user, even more so from a user who has just upgraded from CRT.

Put on HD subscription (DTH or cable) and then you will see the picture quality. It's awesome. The 32 inch HD ready model is an ideal size for HD channels as they generally are 720p.

You can see the attached pictures for estimating picture quality, the second one is from YouTube at 720p.

From the experience I had at Xiaomi Service Center with my phone, I can gladly tell you can trust it's service.

After the update, the sound quality is subtly improved.

The best thing about this is, you can even cast your laptop using chrome, I don't think others provide this application.

Amazon Prime is soon to be supported and Netflix isn't. I can live with that.

Don't worry if you don't find any music apps in play store. Just tell Google assistant what you wanna play and it will play in whatever app you want, be it gaana, Saavn or wynk.

So yeah, no complaints so far. I would advice you to use a stabilizer IF you are using government's electricity service.

And yes, don't book your installation on Sunday even if it shows it's available, they are not.

To those who are saying you can't make AV or any of the HDMI as default. Go to APPS - Live TV, add this to favorites, so you can directly access cable from interface. Now in Patchwall whichever mode you will select, will be set as default when you open Live TV app from interface, there you go!

Go for it!

Title: Upgrading old 2.5" SATA HDD to SSD? then go for it.
Review:
I have an old laptop(8yr old, 2013 model HP probook 4441s) which lags now a days because of its slow spinning 5400RPM SATA HDD. Thought of upgrade my laptop itself and realized that I have to spent 60K for the latest one. So decided to give chance for my old laptop by upgrading it's RAM and HDD.

Since it's an old laptop it doesn't have a m.2 or nvme SSD slot in its board. So bought this 2.5" SSD which will perfectly fit in my 2.5" inch SATA HDD slot. I was in doubt when I bought this whether it will work or not. Trust me this thing worked like a charm.!!! Now my laptop is superfast (as compared to my old HDD) and windows 10 boots up in few seconds. And also launching apps accessing huge files became much much faster. Now I feel like it's a new laptop.!!!

Only problem was how to clone my old HDD and OS without loosing license and data. But crucial site has all the support you need. They have step by step videos to install and upgrade your old laptop. I am not a laptop mechanic, still am able to replace my HDD myself (see the pics). They have cloning software which is free for us(there are third-party sw which does the cloning but we have to pay). Very easy to upgrade by following those docs/videos.

Extremely happy for this purchase. Saved my 50K (not required to buy new laptop)

Conclusion:
If you have a old laptop with slow HDD and you don't have plan to buy new laptop or looking for cheap solution, then go for this SSD.

Title: Dont fall for the Bestseller mark by Amazon. Its a sub-standard product
Review: \n Consistency is watery, not thick or buttery, which is the major downfall of this product, it is not peanut butter its peanut water with some peanut pieces. No added sugar, which is the best part. But PINTOLA SHOULD mention that they have added water in this product. And trust me the real peanut butter should be like butter, not like this sub-standard product. I think they have adulterated this peanut butter with water and surprisingly the price is also bit on the higher side. The packaging is good, no spilling, taste was also good and received a fresh stock. Since I am paying for the peanut and not the water, this makes my first and last purchase from pintola. I recommend saffola (cheaper) or alpino (almost same range as this).\n

Title: Top-Notch Performance & Extremely light weight.
Review:
Bought it for 2,099/- on 2nd May 2021.
Please Read full review only if you are getting black screen error after replacing HDD to caddy and SSD to laptop.

- Before SSD, Boot up time (2-3 mins till Desktop Screen), After SSD (10-16 seconds till Desktop Screen).
- Extremely light weight, even lighter than mobile chargers.
- Getting High speed. In Caddy it gives me (551 read & 549 write speed).
- Used it in original slot and placed HDD in caddy, because Windows was unable to boot it from caddy.
- Used Macrium Free Software for cloning.

In my case I was unable to boot up from SSD due to BIOS and some computer issue, after successful cloning OS to SSD, when I replaced it, windows unable to load up OS properly and shows Black Screen with White Rectangle issue. So once again I formatted my SSD (MBR partition Style) and installed new Windows Using Pen-Drive (Media Creation Tool) , and my issue got resolved, windows got installed in *New SSD within 1 hour* .
Then I deletes my OS and reserved partition from HDD and add-on that space to HDD.

Title: TOOO SMALL!!!!!!!! And no, that's not a feature.
Review:
Easy to hold - For a 5 yr old kid, yes.
For Gaming - Use this mouse as a ball while playing cricket.

If you're a grown adult looking for a mouse for literally any purpose, whether normal usage or gaming, buy anything except this mouse. The ratings on this mouse are appealing but it's a huge letdown. Go buy some other brand which offers normal sized mouse at nearly the same price. Don't buy this mouse if you're >5 yrs old.

Title: A must have book to teach handwriting to kids
